Title: Assam Agarwood Incense Sticks - No Filler, Ethical and Fair Trade

Description:
Discover the rich, calming aroma of our Assam Agarwood Incense Sticks, made with high-quality agarwood sourced from Nagaland, Arunachal and Assam, India. These incense sticks are handcrafted by a local craftsman, Tajul Bakshi, who is an expert in agarwood distillation and uses agarwood dust to create high-quality incense sticks in small batches. Each stick burns for about 15 minutes, making it perfect for quick meditation sessions, yoga or simply to create a peaceful ambiance in your home.

Our incense sticks are made with only natural ingredients, including agarwood powder and agar-agar as a binder, and contain no fillers. They come packaged in a beautiful cardboard box, making them a great gift for loved ones or for your own personal use.

We take pride in sourcing our agarwood directly from local artisans like Tajul Bakshi, who believe in the art of craftsmanship and ensuring ethical, bio, and fair trade practices. By purchasing our incense sticks, you are not only supporting small-scale artisans but also promoting sustainable and eco-friendly practices.

Features:
- Made with high-quality agarwood sourced from Nagaland, Arunachal and Assam
- Handcrafted in small batches by expert craftsman Tajul Bakshi
- Contains no fillers or synthetic ingredients
- Comes packaged in a beautiful cardboard box
- Ethical, bio and fair trade practices
- 31 sticks per box, each stick burns for 15 minutes

Instructions:
Light the tip of the incense stick and gently blow out the flame. Place the stick in an incense holder or any heat-resistant surface and enjoy the calming aroma of our Assam Agarwood Incense Sticks.

Experience the therapeutic benefits of natural agarwood incense with our ethically-sourced, small-batch incense sticks. Order now and discover the beauty of Assam Agarwood Incense Sticks.
